tachyon

Class TachyonURI

  • java.lang.Object
    • tachyon.TachyonURI
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<TachyonURI>

    public final class TachyonURI
extends Object
implements Comparable<TachyonURI>
    It uses a hierarchical URI internally. URI requires that String is escaped, TachyonURI does not. Does not support fragment or query in the URI.

      • TachyonURI

        public TachyonURI(String pathStr)
        Construct a TachyonURI from a String. Path strings are URIs, but with unescaped elements and some additional normalization.
        Parameters:
        pathStr - path to construct the TachyonURI from

      • TachyonURI

        public TachyonURI(String scheme,
          String authority,
          String path)
        Construct a TachyonURI from components.
        Parameters:
        scheme - the scheme of the path. e.g. tachyon, hdfs, s3, file, null, etc.
        authority - the authority of the path. e.g. localhost:19998, 203.1.2.5:8080
        path - the path component of the URI. e.g. /abc/c.txt, /a b/c/c.txt

      • getDepth

        public int getDepth()
        Return the number of elements of the path component of the TachyonURI. 
         /                                  = 0
 /a                                 = 1
 /a/b/c.txt                         = 3
 /a/b/                              = 3
 a/b                                = 2
 a\b                                = 2
 tachyon://localhost:1998/          = 0
 tachyon://localhost:1998/a         = 1
 tachyon://localhost:1998/a/b.txt   = 2
 C:\a                               = 1
 C:                                 = 0
        Returns:
        the depth

      • getLeadingPath

        public String getLeadingPath(int n)
        Get the first n components of the TachyonURI path. There is no trailing separator as the path will be normalized by normalizePath(). 
         /a/b/c, 0              = /
 /a/b/c, 1              = /a
 /a/b/c, 2              = /a/b
 /a/b/c, 3              = /a/b/c
 /a/b/c, 4              = null
        Parameters:
        n - identifies the number of path components to get
        Returns:
        the first n path components, null if the path has less than n components
